<div id="review_4390996704" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4390996704" />
    <a title="Claire Bourdon" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/123827069-claire-bourdon"><img alt="Claire Bourdon" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1639235041p2/123827069.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4390996704?book_show_action=true">Dec 28, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Claire Bourdon" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Claire Bourdon" href="/user/show/123827069-claire-bourdon">Claire Bourdon</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Mass Market Paperback 9782070393565" href="/book/show/435591.Le_Livre_de_ma_m_re">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4390996704" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17568578618881397783">4.5/5 Book of my mother is a son&apos;s testimony to his deceased mother.<br/>This little novel is like a walk where whistles a poetic musicality on a path dotted with emotions, affectionate memories but especially regrets for not having been able to say during his lifetime, all the love he had for his mother.<br/>The author chains paragraphs where words honor at every moment his mother, an isolated mother, locked in by the passion she devotes to her son, idealizing her beloved child, flourishing him with prai</span>
  <span id="freeText17568578618881397783" style="display:none">4.5/5 Book of my mother is a son's testimony to his deceased mother.<br />This little novel is like a walk where whistles a poetic musicality on a path dotted with emotions, affectionate memories but especially regrets for not having been able to say during his lifetime, all the love he had for his mother.<br />The author chains paragraphs where words honor at every moment his mother, an isolated mother, locked in by the passion she devotes to her son, idealizing her beloved child, flourishing him with praise, and covering him with an exclusive maternal love to the point of sacrificing her life as a woman.<br />"No son really knows that his mother will die, and all sons grow angry and impatient with their mothers, madmen that they are, but so swiftly punished."</span>
  <a data-text-id="17568578618881397783" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


