<div id="review_573391308" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/573391308" />
    <a title="Selim Bekar" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/18818151-selim-bekar"><img alt="Selim Bekar" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/573391308?book_show_action=true">Mar 28, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Selim Bekar" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Selim Bekar" href="/user/show/18818151-selim-bekar">Selim Bekar</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer573391308" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3847665877612929701">One of the best books I’ve read in my life. The English version is really good (Not as good as the French one though) Every time I read it, once or twice a year usually, I shed tears. Cohen’s description of losing your mom is completely true and the words he is using are just as true as the feelings he is expressing. You can feel the pain (but also enjoy the joyful moments they (Cohen and his mom) spent together) the book is also really interesting from a historical stand point. It’s a must read</span>
  <span id="freeText3847665877612929701" style="display:none">One of the best books I’ve read in my life. The English version is really good (Not as good as the French one though) Every time I read it, once or twice a year usually, I shed tears. Cohen’s description of losing your mom is completely true and the words he is using are just as true as the feelings he is expressing. You can feel the pain (but also enjoy the joyful moments they (Cohen and his mom) spent together) the book is also really interesting from a historical stand point. It’s a must read for all the French literature lovers but it is a good read for anyone, it depicts the simple and complicated relationship between kids and their parents and is for sure worth a couple of hours and a few tears. Be ready to cry, to call your parents (if they are still alive), and to think and think and thing again.<br />Sélim Bekar</span>
  <a data-text-id="3847665877612929701" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


